-- Kazakhstan Probes Attack on Journalist, Prosecutors Say
-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 2012-04-20T13:48:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/kazakhstan-probes-attack-on-journalist-prosecutors-say.html
Kazakhstan began investigating an
attempt to kill a Uralsk-based reporter, who was remains
hospitalized after a knife and gun attack.  Lukpan Akhmedyarov, a journalist with the Uralskaya Nedelya
newspaper, was assaulted on the streets of Uralsk yesterday by
unidentified men, the Prosecutor General’s Office said today in
an e-mailed statement. The reporter is hospitalized after being
cut eight times with a knife and wounded twice with a gun, the
prosecutors said.  Akhmedyarov’s wife and his editor-in-chief said they
believe the murder attempt was related to the reporter’s
professional activity, Novosti Kazakhstan  reported  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
